# Unfixed UBI9 RPM CVEs — mirrors .grype.yaml fix-state:not-fixed rule.
# Trivy has no per-type ignore-unfixed scope, so we list unfixed OS CVEs here.
# Re-review when Red Hat ships a fixed libpng for RHEL 9.

# libpng 2:1.6.37-15.el9_8 — unfixed upstream, no patch available
CVE-2026-22020

# openssl: Heap UAF in PKCS7_verify() — ubi9-minimal not yet rebuilt with fix
# Affects enricher/crawler only. Not exploitable: app code doesn't call PKCS7_verify.
# Remove when Red Hat publishes a patched ubi9-minimal image.
CVE-2026-45447

# python3-pip-wheel 21.3.1-2.el9_8 — unfixed upstream, no patched RPM yet.
# Affects enricher/crawler only. Not exploitable: CVE is in pip's
# console_scripts/gui_scripts entry-point path handling; images install deps via
# uv at build time and never run pip on untrusted input at runtime.
# Remove when Red Hat ships a fixed python3-pip-wheel for RHEL 9.
CVE-2026-8643
